## Summary

Extends the `GraphStore` trait (defined in `domain::traits`) with
versioned checkpoint reads and ships concrete impls on every
production `GraphStore` in the workspace. The default trait
implementations **panic with the concrete type name** (D7: loud
failure > silent ignore). The `CachedGraphStore` is the only impl
that delegates to the real `VersionedGraphCache` ring; the others
expose a single-version stub (id 1, current graph).

A new `StoreError::CheckpointNotFound(CheckpointId)` variant
distinguishes a cold store from an evicted id.

A new `CheckpointId` value object lives in the domain layer
(`domain::value_objects::CheckpointId`); `infrastructure::graph::checkpoint`
re-exports it for backward compat with PR-1.

6 new integration tests in `tests/checkpoint_integration.rs` cover
the full snapshot-isolation invariant at the `GraphStore` trait
boundary, including a 10-thread Ă— 100-read concurrent consistency
test.

`docs/adr/ADR-035-graph-checkpointing.md` is the full ADR (329 lines,
ADR-032/034 style).

