## Backward Compatibility

- All 35 slow-path tool readers of `load_graph()` continue to work
  (the new trait methods are additive, not modifying the existing
  6 methods).
- All 56 hot-path readers of `analysis_service.graph_cache().get()`
  continue to work (no changes to `GraphCache` public API beyond
  the additions from PR-1).
- The panicking default impls are intentionally loud. Stores that
  do not override will panic at runtime if any caller invokes
  `current_checkpoint_id()` or `checkpoint_at()`. This is a
  deliberate "test the migration path" decision; the call sites in
  the MCP server currently don't call these methods, so no
  production panic is expected.
- `CachedGraphStore` is the only `GraphStore` impl wired into
  `HandlerContext::get_graph_store()`. The new methods on
  `CachedGraphStore` are exercised by the integration tests; the
  in-server call path remains unchanged for the existing 35 tools.

## Risks

- **Default panicking impls can mask silent bugs** in stores that
  nobody calls. If a future store is added and a caller expects
  `current_checkpoint_id()` to return `None` instead of panicking,
  the panic will surface in production. This is by design (D7) and
  the alternative (silently return `None`) is the worse failure mode.
- **Layer boundary**: `CheckpointId` was moved from
  `infrastructure::graph` to `domain::value_objects`. PR-1 callers
  that use `crate::infrastructure::graph::checkpoint::CheckpointId`
  continue to work because the type is re-exported. Callers that
  matched on the previous private `u64` field of the struct
  (impossible â€” it was `pub` from day one) would break, but no
  such callers exist in the codebase.
- **PR-1's `get_ref()` leak is unchanged** (out of scope for PR-2).
  Tracked for a future ADR.
- **5 pre-existing test failures** (PG roundtrip, aix_handlers
  manifest tests, scan classify, graph analytics god_nodes) are
  unrelated to ADR-035. Confirmed by reproducing on the stashed
  pre-PR-2 tree.

